reviewText: As funny as I remember it- it's a little dated but still a great movie. Two scenes that stick out- the cobbler and the scene at Bastogne, when the American was attacking from one side, the German the other- describing how the battle took place.
Still as funny as it was when I first saw it in 1969.
I thought it was great! Just as good this time around as it was when it first came out!
It's not quite as funny as I remembered; but cute and the price was right.
As funny now as it was when I saw it in the theatre in the 60's

I'm very happy with my purchase. I have seen the movie before,  it is an old favorite so I knew I liked the movie, dated as it is it's still fun. It's nice to see so many people who would later become some of my favorite actors when they were young and virtually unknown.  The thing I was worried about was the quality of the DVD. I have occasionally purchased a DVD only to find that the quality of the picture is not good. I can say that the quality of this DVD is very good including close captioning.
Have not seen for years, funny, hard to find DVD
my friend was delighted with returning to a favorite part of his world.
Fun to watch again... I had a small walk on extra part.
If you remember the early 70s and have traveled, you will adore this movie. Hilarious, and with Suzanne Pleshette, plus a scene at a youth hostel with Donovan singing. Fun movie.
Great movie with good actors and good scenes inside major European countries.
This is an old favorite.
I loved this movie, stellar cast, a great time capsule of the 60's.

I live in Germany.
I couldn't GET a lot of time off from work, so...
I bought a sight-seeing EUROPEAN bus-tour,
for my oldest niece, and my mother.
Very enjoyable. Reminds me of my husband's and my own tour in some ways.
An oldie but goodie.  I saw this movie when it first came out.  Still relevant and fun.  Makes the point that to be a good traveler - less is more.
It was fun to see this film again that I had seen when it first came out. Brought back a lot of memories and laughs.
Just a fun old chick flick! I liked it!! I always remembers it to be funny!

Great movie, experiences I lived through and enjoyed.  But likely only appreciated by those who were actually there in Europe 10-15  years after WWII.  A few of the actors went on to become famous later in their careers.
very disappointing it was boring and dated  and i love old movies
